In re WHEELER. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 28, 1903.) No. 74. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Eugene Freyer, for appellant. O. C. Brown, for respondent.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

Appeal dismissed in open court upon the ground that petition for review should have been filed, instead of appeal taken.
